content.description: Climb starts up a tall, tricky slab that leads to left, bowing crack. Spicy bolt spacing down low.
content.protection: Bolts to ring anchors. Lower off.
content.location: Second from the left on the right face just right of a small grove of trees on the highest portion of talus.

content.description: Tallest climb on Fissures Right. Starts on the obvious, horizontal rail under a shallow roof that leads to a cruxy, intro sequence to gain a blocky jug. From there, continue up the tall, enjoyable slab to the headwall. After clipping the third bolt on the gentle overhang, split left onto excellent climbing on good rock to the highest anchors on the wall, whereas Luminous Flesh Giant goes right and immediately clip its chains.
content.location: Same start as Luminous Flesh Giant. Third climb from the left on Fissures Right, just left of a couple trees hugging the cliff.
